<h4>Guidelines for Creating Documents with Respect to Style</h4>

<p>Use the following guidelines when creating documents so that your documents
can be easily published on the Internet. Remember:</p>

<ul class="disc">

<li>Decide on a text font size and font style for the whole document and
define it utilizing styles. Within styles, this is called "Normal"ù or
 "Body text."ù</li>

<li>If you want any part of your document to have different font or spacing
other than what you have defined for "Normal" or "body text,‚" create a
new style element with that change and select the new style for that part. Do
not embed font changes within the document. In other words, do not highlight
text and change the font for the highlighted text.</li>

<li>Determine distance between paragraphs by defining the line spacing
 "before and after"ù within the style instead of adding blank lines between 
paragraphs.</li>

<li>When creating numbered or bulleted lists create a new style entry that
is formatted with numbers or bullets.</li>

<li>Avoid the use of tabs. Either define a style that is indented or use
tables to put text in columns.</li>
</ul>

